The paper proposes a novel SpatioTemporal Multi-Agent Reinforcement Learning (STMARL) framework for traffic light control, which involves the use of artificial intelligence and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of deep Q-learning method, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the coordination of multiple traffic lights, which involves the use of robotics and control systems, falling under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves the use of recurrent neural networks and graph neural networks, which fall under the categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), respectively.
